  "HEADLINE": "Of the 2 wobble driver(s) SpCas9-NGG missed (['TP53_R175H', 'TP53_R273H']), 2 are rescued by an alt enzyme (['TP53_R175H', 'TP53_R273H']); none left unrescued. Combining SpCas9-NGG + NG + Cas12a, 7/7 wobble drivers are DNA-addressable with a designed allele-specific guide. Rescues come via SEED (G>A destroys a G / makes an A, so it rarely CREATES an NG or TTTV PAM) \u2014 the wider NG PAM density supplies a nearby PAM that puts the SNV in the seed, exactly the engineered purpose of SpCas9-NG.",
  "CEILING": [
    "CDS-local; SEED near exon edges needs intron-aware genomic confirmation; PAM_CREATED codon-local-robust.",
    "Relaxed PAMs (NG esp.) raise genome-wide OFF-target liability -> PAM+seed available is necessary NOT sufficient; real allele-specific cutting + off-target profile = wet-lab residual; NG/Cas12a on-target efficiency is context-dependent and generally below NGG.",
    "enAsCas12a (TTYN) / SpRY (near-PAMless) relax further but worsen the off-target trade -> not scanned."
  ]
